column1: # Shortfin Mako Shark (Isurus oxyrinchus) Growth Data - VERIFIED FROM PDF SOURCES
# This CSV contains age-length-weight data derived from VALIDATED von Bertalanffy
# and Gompertz growth parameters published in peer-reviewed studies.
# 1. Each row includes source_pdf and pdf_reference columns
# 2. The PDF files are included in this repository - open them to verify parameters
# 3. Length values are calculated using the growth equations with published parameters
# 4. Weight is calculated using: W(kg) = 4.4e-6 * FL(cm)^3.14 (Kohler et al. 1996)
#    Citation: Natanson LJ et al. (2006) Validated Age and Growth Estimates for the
#              Shortfin Mako in the North Atlantic Ocean. Environ Biol Fish 77:367-383
#    Citation: Semba Y et al. (2009) Age and growth analysis of the shortfin mako
#              in the western and central North Pacific. Environ Biol Fish 84:377-391
#    Note: PCL converted to FL using: FL = 1.10*PCL + 8.1 (Bishop 2004)
#    Citation: Groeneveld JC et al. (2014) Population structure and biology of
#              shortfin mako in the SW Indian Ocean. Marine Freshwater Res 65:1045-1058
# Source: Kohler NE et al. (1996) NOAA Tech. Memo. NMFS-NE-110
# Von Bertalanffy: L(t) = L_inf - (L_inf - L0) * exp(-K * t)
# Gompertz: L(t) = L_inf * exp(ln(L0/L_inf) * exp(-K * t))
